    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/morrison-vv-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are consistent with MRL 2 scoping decisions given medium model influence and high decision consequence. CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index demonstrate sufficient accuracy (MAE 6.3%, all predictions within experimental uncertainty) to support identification of worst-case operating conditions. The governing submission requirement Q-HEM-001 (documented in package as hasRequirement) is addressed through the validation evidence. The model is accepted for use in the 510(k) submission to support worst-case hemolysis operating condition identification for the Class II CPB device.",
